</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR65:v97#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR65"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              65-&#xA;                CHAPTERED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div width="100%" style="text-align:center;"><div id="bill_num_title_chap"><span style="text-align:center;font-weight:bold;font-size:1.1em;font-family:'Times New Roman'; "><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              
                        No. 65</b></span></div><div style="text-align:center;padding-top: 1.0em;padding-bottom: 1.2em;" id="chap_num_title_chap"><span style="font-size:1.4em;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;">
                      CHAPTER 122</span></div></div><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to California Fairgrounds Appreciation Month. </span></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center">
                  
                  [<span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Filed with
              </span><span style="  font-size: 1.3em">
                Secretary of State
              </span> <span style="font-size: 13pt">July 03, 2025.
                      </span>]
                </div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 65, Alvarado-Gil.
                          California Fairgrounds Appreciation Month.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would designate the month of May 2025 as California Fairgrounds Appreciation Month in appreciation for the services provided to California by the 77 fairgrounds in the state.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_39E21FC1-A5C4-49C8-9A3E-1786DB1B40A3"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The history of fairgrounds in California dates back to the mid-19th century, a time when communities were beginning to take shape in the rapidly developing state. These fairs quickly grew in popularity as they provided a platform for farmers, artisans, and inventors to display their innovations; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B92605E4-D500-4011-A2E2-5D7F9AC425C7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The earliest recorded fair in California was held in 1854 in the City of San Francisco, where agricultural exhibitions were organized to showcase local produce and livestock; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_04A890F4-526D-46EE-BCF8-D98C84B29A10"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Over time, the tradition of holding fairs spread throughout the state, with each region developing its own unique flavor and focus. These early fairs laid the groundwork for what would become a beloved institution in California’s cultural heritage; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_01638B68-FFF8-4AEB-B29F-2B2E9490C68F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California’s 77 fairgrounds serve the entire state, from the County of San Diego to the County of Del Norte, and from the County of Monterey to the County of Mariposa; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5DB29562-5704-496B-BCEF-D7110A7D60B0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California counties enjoy the year-round economic, recreational, cultural, and social impacts of their local fairgrounds; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_4885A929-B46B-4B95-BF14-2E0915B9574B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds play a crucial role in economic development and business growth by serving as vibrant hubs for community engagement, commerce, and tourism, and are pivotal in nurturing economic vitality and fostering a thriving business ecosystem across the state; and </div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_46B059D4-97B0-408B-B314-50326ACB286A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds host a wide array of events, from county fairs and agricultural expositions to concerts, trade shows, and festivals, attracting millions of visitors annually. This influx of visitors stimulates local economies by driving demand for hospitality services, including hotels, restaurants, and retail establishments; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C466D4C6-62F1-4EAB-B2A9-4B3EA2B4917E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds provide businesses with unique opportunities to showcase products, launch new offerings, and engage directly with consumers, fostering brand visibility and market expansion. In addition, fairgrounds often partner with local educational institutions to promote agricultural education and innovation, contributing to workforce development in key sectors; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_079548DF-A497-4790-9C33-82FFE142ACF4"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds expend and generate hundreds of millions of new dollars for nonprofit organizations, youth organizations, cities and counties, small businesses, and the state’s General Fund; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_3BA6F98F-C4B7-4B42-9FEC-663952D1703D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds serve as a communal hub where people from all walks of life come together to share experiences and create memories; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_32EA6462-8578-45E8-A746-1371ECF852E1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds offer a space for community engagement and interaction, where the bonds of friendship and community are strengthened. From the thrilling rides and games to the educational exhibits and competitions, fairgrounds provide entertainment and learning opportunities for all ages; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A0206369-F7F3-437B-BAC1-C3C9C70CDD90"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairgrounds are a place where tradition and modernity meet, offering a glimpse into both the history and the future of California’s diverse communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_8D7BF7B9-3B18-47A9-922A-065A90535633"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California’s fairgrounds provide safe public facilities specifically designed for animals, pets, and livestock during good times and bad; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_9D5BC94B-ABCE-4D25-8630-92551A286F62"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, One of the primary functions of fairgrounds is to celebrate and preserve California’s rich agricultural heritage and emphasize the significance of agriculture, helping to ensure that this vital industry continues to thrive; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6E3CF308-EF53-47E5-82B5-0774FE8F3269"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Fairs offer a platform for programs foundational to the agricultural education of youth, such as Future Farmers of America (FFA) and the National 4-H Council, to educate the public and students by hosting displays of livestock, produce, and horticulture. These events offer insight into sustainable farming practices and the latest advancements in agricultural technology; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_AA195D4E-5B0D-4FF7-9E2B-290D61B491F1"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Competitions, such as those for best livestock or produce, encourage excellence and innovation in the agricultural sector; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_B1CF99B7-ECF4-427B-98BF-A709D320035C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, During a state of emergency, a natural disaster, or the ongoing impacts of climate change, California fairgrounds are called into service as medical sites, staging areas for emergency equipment and emergency personnel, and evacuation sites to assist those displaced by a fire or flood; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_DD379D8E-AE7D-4CCE-9EC4-9D436F02C672"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The future of fairgrounds lies in their ability to adapt to changing social and economic landscapes while preserving the traditions that make them so beloved. As California continues to grow and evolve, so too must these iconic venues; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_38EFE69B-4CFA-4B0D-BF28-EB02B2E56C5C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Investments in infrastructure and technology will be crucial to maintaining the relevance and appeal of fairgrounds; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_1923E4C5-61CF-4BE0-AE8B-369D3B8F5255"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California’s 77 fairgrounds continue to serve as the recreational, social, and economic hubs of their respective communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_C7653786-8448-4D3E-96F5-C6ECF95F700F"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, By continuing to provide a space for community gathering, economic activity, and cultural celebration, fairgrounds will remain an integral part of California’s identity. They are not just a part of the state’s history but a vibrant and essential element of its future; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_32B41DD9-4849-457B-924D-FBC84C7F5723"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby designates the month of May 2025 as California Fairgrounds Appreciation Month in appreciation for the services provided to California by the 77 fairgrounds in the state; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_1CF4B949-D124-49BA-A723-5B845660428E"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Legislature extends its warmest regards and appreciation to the thousands of fair volunteers, directors, CEOs, and staff, business supporters, sponsors, and associations who keep the network of California fairgrounds strong, vibrant, relevant, and successful; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_8BCCBA82-4E13-4DAA-892D-043F420216CA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
